---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { AUTHOR, CMP_SOURCE_REPO, SITE_TITLE } from '../../../consts';

const pageTitle = `Context Minimization Principle (CMP) — Research — ${SITE_TITLE}`;
const pageDescription =
	'A living research book on context cost, correct modification, and AI-era software design.';
const canonicalHref = new URL('/research/cmp/', Astro.site).href;

const coverImage = 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1451187580459-43490279c0fa?w=1920&q=80';

const bookJsonLd = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@type': 'Book',
	name: 'Context Minimization Principle',
	description: pageDescription,
	url: canonicalHref,
	author: {
		'@type': 'Person',
		name: 'Lianghui Zhang',
		url: AUTHOR.social.github,
	},
	inLanguage: 'en',
	bookFormat: 'https://schema.org/EBook',
};

const bibtex = `@book{zhang2026cmp,
  title = {Context Minimization Principle},
  author = {Lianghui Zhang},
  year = {2026},
  url = {${canonicalHref}},
  note = {Living book, version 0.1}
}`;
---

<BaseLayout
	title={pageTitle}
	description={pageDescription}
	image={coverImage}
	canonicalHref={canonicalHref}
	jsonLd={bookJsonLd}
>
	<section class="cmp-hero">
		<p class="kicker">Online book · Living · v0.1</p>
		<h1>Context Minimization Principle</h1>
		<p class="subtitle">
			A living research book on context cost, correct modification, and AI-era software design.
		</p>
		<div class="hero-meta">
			<span>Lianghui Zhang</span>
			<span>·</span>
			<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="license noopener noreferrer"
				>License: CC BY 4.0</a
			>
			<span>·</span>
			<a href={CMP_SOURCE_REPO} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Paper repo ↗</a>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="cmp-section">
		<h2>Who is this for?</h2>
		<p>
			This book is for software architects, senior engineers, AI coding tool builders, and researchers asking a
			shared question: what makes a codebase easier for humans and AI agents to modify correctly?
		</p>
		<p>
			The central problem is not whether AI can generate code. The harder problem is whether a system makes the
			required context for a correct modification discoverable, bounded, and trustworthy.
		</p>
		<p>
			CMP gives this problem a vocabulary: context cost, sufficient context, depth, breadth, modification closure,
			and context operators. It treats software design as the discipline of making future modification cheaper,
			safer, and more reliable.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="cmp-section">
		<h2>Start here</h2>
		<p>
			Begin with the root essay. It explains why AI coding agents make software design more important, not less.
		</p>
		<p>
			<a href="/research/cmp/foundations/why-ai-agents/"
				>Why AI Agents Force a New Theory of Software Design →</a
			>
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="cmp-section">
		<h2>Coming next</h2>
		<ol class="toc-list">
			<li>The Long Context Fallacy</li>
			<li>Future AI Design Still Optimizes Context</li>
			<li>Software Design Is for Modification</li>
			<li>Correct Modification Requires Sufficient Context</li>
		</ol>
	</section>

	<section class="cmp-section">
		<h2>Research map</h2>
		<p class="muted">
			CMP is published as a living research book. The structure will evolve as the theory becomes clearer.
		</p>
		<ul class="two-col">
			<li>
				<strong>The AI moment:</strong> why agents expose context acquisition as the real bottleneck.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>The core theory:</strong> modification, sufficient context, and context cost.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>The shape of context cost:</strong> depth, breadth, and modification closure.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Design vocabulary:</strong> principles, boundaries, tests, languages, and architecture as context
				operators.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Agent operability:</strong> designing codebases that AI agents can modify reliably.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Measurement:</strong> Context-Footprint, agent traces, and empirical studies.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="cmp-section">
		<h2>Cite this book</h2>
		<p class="muted">Suggested plain citation:</p>
		<blockquote class="cite-block">
			Lianghui Zhang, <em>Context Minimization Principle</em> (living online book), 2026. {canonicalHref}
		</blockquote>
		<p class="muted">BibTeX:</p>
		<pre class="bib"><code>{bibtex}</code></pre>
	</section>

	<section class="cmp-section">
		<h2>License</h2>
		<p>
			Unless otherwise noted, <em>Context Minimization Principle</em> by Lianghui Zhang is licensed under
			<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="license noopener noreferrer"
				>Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International</a
			>.
		</p>
		<p class="muted">
			This license applies to the CMP online book content, not to the website source code or third-party assets.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="cmp-section subscribe">
		<h2>Subscribe</h2>
		<p>
			<a href="/research/cmp/rss.xml">CMP-only RSS</a>
			<span class="dot">·</span>
			<a href="/rss.xml">Blog RSS</a> (unchanged; blog posts only)
		</p>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.cmp-hero {
		padding: 40px 0 32px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
		margin-bottom: 36px;
	}
	.kicker {
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--accent);
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}
	.cmp-hero h1 {
		font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 48px);
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
		max-width: 900px;
	}
	.subtitle {
		font-size: 18px;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: var(--secondary);
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}
	.hero-meta {
		font-size: 14px;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px;
	}
	.cmp-section {
		margin-bottom: 40px;
		max-width: 900px;
	}
	.cmp-section h2 {
		font-size: 22px;
		margin-bottom: 14px;
	}
	.cmp-section p {
		color: var(--primary);
		line-height: 1.7;
	}
	.muted {
		color: var(--secondary);
		font-size: 15px;
	}
	.two-col {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
		gap: 14px 28px;
		margin: 0;
		padding-left: 20px;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}
	.toc-list {
		margin: 0;
		padding-left: 20px;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}
	.toc-list li {
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}
	.cite-block {
		margin: 12px 0 20px;
		font-size: 15px;
	}
	.bib {
		font-size: 13px;
		line-height: 1.5;
		overflow-x: auto;
	}
	.subscribe .dot {
		margin: 0 10px;
		color: var(--text-muted);
	}
</style>
